s-Overland,\n19% Missouri Pacific, 57%, up\nGeneral Electric, 106, up 1; South\nern Pacific, 113%. off Kansas\nCity Southern, 60%, up Mack\nTruck, 103. off Yellow Truck,\n31% Middle* States Oil. 3%. up\nGeneral Railway Signal, 118%, up\n1: Atchison, l|p, off Baldwin,\n227%, up 1% Radio, 53%, up\nB. 0., 117%, off American\nCan, 55%, off American Loco\nmotive, 109, off General Motors,\n200%. off New Haven, 54%, up\nMarland, 34%, off Hudson\nMotors, 82%, off Transconti\nnental Oil, 9, up\nNational Tea Co.\nSales Increase\nNational Tea Co. sales for May\ntotaled $4,412,567, compared with\n$4,402,874 for the corresponding\nmonth last year. For the first five\nmonths of the present year sales\ntotaled $23,023,011, compared with\n$22,141,923 for the corresponding\nperiod last year.\nNew York Cotton\nNEW YORK\u2014Cotton opened five to\nseven points lower. July 16.64, off 6:\nOctober 17.01, off 6; December 17.22, off\n7; January 17.29, off 5; March 17.49, off\n5; May 17.57, off 6.\nGrain Futures\nWHEAT.\nPrevious\nHigh. Low. Close. Close.\nJuly 1.46 1.45% 1.45% 1.46%\nSept 1.43% 1.42% 1.42% 1-43%\nCORN.\nPrevious\nHigh, Low. Close. Close.\nJuly 1.00% 99% 1.00% 1.00%\nSept 1.06 1.05% 1.05% 1.05%\ni OATS.\nPrevious\nHigh. Low. Close. Close.\nJuly 48% 48% 48% 48%\nSept 48% 47% 48 48y s\nRYE.\nj Previous\nHign, Low. Close. Close.\nJuly 1.19 1.18% 1.19 1.18%\nSept 1.04% 1.04% 1.04% 1.04%\nAttractive\n6% Bonds\nINVESTORS have found that bonds we rec\nommend are not only safe, but are suited to\ntheir special requirements. The customer\u2019s in\nterest must come first.\nIf the customer needs a high degree of safety,\nhe can get it through Schroeder First Mort\ngage Bonds. And the income is as large as is\nconsistent with safety.\nAnother feature of these good bonds is their\nready marketability, yet they bring an annual\nreturn of 6%.\nWe will be glad to tell you all the points about\nSchroeder bonds which have made them such\nan attractive form of investment.\nDenominations: SI,